senses.sense: The 3<sup>rd</sup> letter of the English alphabet, called cee and written in the Latin script.
The ordinal number 3<sup>rd</sup>, derived from this letter of the English alphabet, called cee and written in the Latin script.
(music) The middle tone in either one of the sets of seven white keys on a keyboard or a set of seven strings on a stringed instrument.
(Internet slang, text messaging) Abbreviation of see; also C.
